    <spirit:maxSlaves>16</spirit:maxSlaves>
    <spirit:description>AMBA AHB addresses the requirements of high-performance synthesizable designs. (Refer AMBA Specification Rev 2.0 - ARM IHI 0011A) It is a bus interface that implements features required for high-performance, high clock frequency systems including :
    - burst transfers
    - split transactions
    - single cycle bus Manager handover
    - single clock edge operation
    - non-tristate implementation
    - wider data bus configurations (64/128 bits).</spirit:description>
